==English==
===Etymology===
From [[exo-]] "outside" + [[thermic]] "of heat"
===Adjective===
'''exothermic'''

#{{chemistry}}: Of a [[chemical]] [[reaction]] that releases [[energy]] in the form of [[heat]].
#{{zoology}}: Of an [[animal]] whose [[body]] [[temperature]] is regulated by [[external]] factors.

===Antonym===
*[[endothermic]]